Parliament, Tuesday, 27 February 2018 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations is tomorrow to be briefed by the Human Sciences Research Council (HSRC) on its research proposals regarding learner transport in South Africa. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 28 February 2018
	Time: 09:30 am
	Venue: Committee Room 3, Upper Ground, 90 Plein street. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS, MS YVONNE PHOSA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za The seat of Parliament is in Cape Town, but it could be moved by an Act of Parliament supported by a majority of the members of the National Assembly.Read more